Reasoning: The paper deals with the decidability of satisfiability for a temporal logic with constraints over various tree-like structures. This involves techniques from model theory, automata theory, and logic. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves combinatorial aspects of tree-like structures, which suggests the sub-category cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of automata and games suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper deals with decidability questions, which suggests the sub-category cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
